# Tech Stack - Python

## Python Stack

**Runtime:** Python 3.13+ (3.11 legacy support), pip (venv only), venv required

### Build base (Docker / CI)

Pin minimums in `requirements.txt` and upgrade before installing deps in Dockerfiles so Trivy/scanning does not flag CVEs in vendored setuptools/wheel.

| Package    | Version    | Purpose |
|------------|------------|---------|
| wheel      | >=0.46.2   | Build backend; CVE-2026-24049 fix |
| setuptools | >=81.0.0   | Build/runtime; vendored jaraco.context CVE-2026-23949 fix |

In Dockerfile builder: (1) run `pip install --no-cache-dir --upgrade pip setuptools wheel` before `pip install -r requirements.txt`; (2) after installing requirements, remove old setuptools-79.x / wheel-0.45.x dist-infos so Trivy only sees fixed versions (see **rg-common/docs/Docker-standards.md** §3 multi-stage Python pattern).

